<subSubSection id="C3546563994B112AFF36FB6FFF00FA76" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF136E8994B112AFF36FB6FFF00FA76" blockId="74.[124,653,897,1771]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
DIAGNOSIS: The more convex outer margins of the pronotum will separate the members of this species from the very similar specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D6B994B112AFE8CFAB7FE03FA8E" authority="OPITZ, 2005" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2005" box="[291,432,1337,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turnbowi" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA994B112AFE8CFAB7FE03FA8E" box="[291,432,1337,1360]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">A. turnbowi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2095781994B112AFE6DFAB7FE4AFA8E" box="[450,505,1337,1360]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Further, the parameres are significantly narrower in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D6B994B112AFDDCFAD9FF7EFA55" authority="OPITZ, 2005" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ebenus" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA994B112AFDDCFAD9FF7EFA55" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">A. ebenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2095781994B112AFF4FFAFAFEAAFA55" box="[224,281,1396,1419]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, than they are in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D6B994B112AFE57FAFAFD36FA55" authority="OPITZ, 2005" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2005" box="[504,645,1396,1419]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turnbowi" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA994B112AFE57FAFAFD36FA55" box="[504,645,1396,1419]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">A. turnbowi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
